From: OctaneOS <octaneos@local>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] typec: phy-switcher: fire HPD-in on DP Configure, not on monitor HPD state

After a warm reboot the monitor may be sleeping with HPD de-asserted.
The phy_switcher's sunxi_phy_mux_set() previously required
DP_STATUS_HPD_STATE=1 from the monitor's VDM Attention before setting
hpd_status=true.  Since the sleeping monitor doesn't send VDM Attention
until something wakes it, and the EDP driver won't attempt AUX until it
sees hpd_status=true, neither side moves first.  The display stays dark
until the user power-cycles the monitor.

The fix: on a DP mode *transition* (Configure VDM completed, mode is
changing), fire hpd_status=true immediately regardless of the monitor's
HPD state.  The EDP driver's existing 30-second AUX retry loop then
wakes the monitor -- the DP spec requires sinks to respond to AUX
requests even in low-power (D3) state.

On Attention messages (same mode, no transition), continue to respect
DP_STATUS_HPD_STATE for correct live hot-plug/unplug detection at
runtime.

The passive cable path (data == NULL, dp_mode == true) already fired
hpd_status=true unconditionally.  This patch makes active Alt Mode
(VDMs present) consistent with that behavior while preserving runtime
HPD signalling.

Confirmed root cause via source analysis:
  - sunxi_phy_mux_set() sets hpd_status=false when HPD=0 on Configure
  - hpd_status != hpd_status_pre is false (both false) -> no extcon event
  - edp_sink_extcon_evt() never fires -> hpd_state_now stays false
  - drm_dp_output_enable() returns RET_FAIL at "sink device unconnect!"
  - EDP driver never starts -> display dark permanently until monitor cycle

Signed-off-by: OctaneOS <octaneos@local>
---
 bsp/drivers/usb/typec/mux/sunxi-phy-switcher.c | 14 +++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/bsp/drivers/usb/typec/mux/sunxi-phy-switcher.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/usb/typec/mux/sunxi-phy-switcher.c
@@ -282,9 +282,18 @@

 		/* altmode displayport plugin */
-		if ((data->conf & DP_CONF_SIGNALING_DP) && (data->status & DP_STATUS_HPD_STATE))
-			phy_switcher->hpd_status = true;
-		else
-			phy_switcher->hpd_status = false;
+		/* altmode displayport plugin.
+		 * On a mode transition (Configure VDM just completed), fire HPD-in
+		 * immediately even if the monitor's HPD is de-asserted -- it may be
+		 * sleeping after a warm reboot.  The EDP driver's AUX retry loop wakes
+		 * it (DP spec requires AUX response even in low-power D3 state).
+		 * On Attention messages (same mode, no transition), respect the monitor's
+		 * HPD state for live hot-plug/unplug detection at runtime. */
+		if (data->conf & DP_CONF_SIGNALING_DP) {
+			if ((data->status & DP_STATUS_HPD_STATE) ||
+			    (phy_switcher->mode != state->mode))
+				phy_switcher->hpd_status = true;
+			else
+				phy_switcher->hpd_status = false;
+		} else {
+			phy_switcher->hpd_status = false;
+		}
